# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — WCWAA Scouting Pipeline
# =============================================================================
# This file tells Git which files/folders to NEVER commit to version control.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#   - Security: credentials (gc_session.json) must never be uploaded to GitHub
#   - Size: venv/ is ~100MB and can be recreated from requirements.txt
#   - Clutter: compiled bytecode and OS files add noise without value
#
# RULE OF THUMB: If a file can be (re)generated from something already committed,
# it should be in .gitignore. Commit the *source*, not the *output*.
# =============================================================================

# --- Python virtual environment ---
# Anyone cloning this repo runs: python3 -m venv venv && pip install -r requirements.txt
venv/
.venv/
env/

# --- Python bytecode cache ---
# Python auto-creates .pyc files when it compiles your scripts. They're machine-
# specific and regenerated automatically — never need to be committed.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# --- Auth / session credentials ---
# gc_session.json holds your GameChanger login cookies. If committed and pushed
# to a public repo, anyone could access your GameChanger account.
# REGENERATE WITH: python3 gc_scraper.py --login
Scripts/gc_session.json

# --- Environment variable files ---
# If we ever add a .env file for API keys or other secrets, exclude it here.
.env
.env.*

# --- macOS system files ---
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# --- VS Code workspace settings ---
# Personal editor preferences — other developers have their own setup.
.vscode/
*.code-workspace

# --- Log files ---
# Logs are runtime artifacts. They're written locally and don't belong in git.
# If you want to track log output, use the Logs/ folder locally only.
Logs/*.log

# --- Output PDFs ---
# Generated PDFs are build artifacts. They're large and change every week.
# Commit the *scripts that generate them*, not the PDFs themselves.
# The examples/ folder is explicitly excluded from this rule (see below).
**/*.pdf
!examples/*.pdf

# --- Game log .txt files (Scorebooks / Games folders) ---
# Play-by-play game files are runtime data, not source code. They're scraped
# fresh each week by gc_scraper.py and live in Google Drive, not in git.
# The examples/ folder is explicitly excluded from this rule (see below).
*/Scorebooks/*.txt
*/Games/*.txt
!examples/*.txt

# --- Root-level test/scratch PDFs ---
dot_size_comparison.pdf
dummy_spray_chart.pdf
sample_v2_approval.pdf
